All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Action0ToAction<T>
    Adapts an Action0 to provide the Action interface.
    BasicStateFactory
    A StateFactory implementation that creates BasicState instances.
    CanProcess<ProcessParameter>
    An EBC that CanProcess is capable of processing input and thus provides an Action to do so.
    CanStart
    An EBC that CanStart can be invoked to perform some work and thus provides an Action0 to do so.
    CollectionsOutputCreator<Input1Element,​Input2Element,​OutputElement>
    This JoinOutputCreator implementation takes two input Collections and creates an output List with one output value for every pair of values in the input collections.
    Configurable
    EBCs that are Configurable can be configured with an arbitrary number of parameters.
    ConstructableOutputCreator<Input1,​Input2,​Output>
    This JoinOutputCreator implementation creates the output by dynamically invoking the given Constructor.
    DependsOn<Dependency>
    An EBC that DependsOn another object, can be explicitly tagged with this interface.
    EntryPoint
    This is a special marker interface that can be used to tag an EBC as the EntryPoint of an application.
    EventToEvent0<T>
    Adapts an Event to provide the Event0 interface.
    Flow
    This class contains some static methods used to start a DSL sentence used to create a flow of EBCs
    FlowExecutor
    The FlowExecuter supports both: Execution of existing flows with one of it's static methods and the execution of flows created per execution using the given FlowFactory.
    FlowFactory
    A factory that can be used to create flow instances.
    GenericJoin<Input1,​Input2,​Output>
    This Join base class joins two input values to an output value that has a constructor taking the two input values as parameters.
    GenericJoinCollections<Input1Element,​Input2Element,​OutputElement>
    This Join base class joins two input collections of the input element types to a collection of the output element type by using a constructor of the output element type taking the two input element type values as parameters.
    GenericJoinObjectAndCollection<Input1,​Input2Element,​OutputElement>
    This Join base class joins a single first input value with a second collection of input elements to a collection of output element by using a constructor of the output element type taking the first input type and the second input element type value as parameters.
    Join<Input1,​Input2,​Output>
    This is a class that can be used to implement Join EBCs.
    JoinBase<Input1,​Input2,​Output>
    This is a base class that can be extended to easily implement custom Joins.
    JoinCollections<Input1Element,​Input2Element,​OutputElement>
    This Join class joins two input collections of the input element types to a collection of the output element type by using a JoinOutputCreator to join the input element types to the output element type.
    JoinInputStorage<Input1,​Input2>
    This class defines a storage that is used by Join implementations to store their input values.
    JoinObjectAndCollection<Input1,​Input2Element,​OutputElement>
    This Join class joins a single first input value with a second collection of input elements to a collection of output element by using a JoinOutputCreator to join the first input type and the second input element type to the output element type.
    JoinOutputCreator<Input1,​Input2,​Output>
    This interface describes objects capable of creating output for Joins.
    JoinProcessAndSignal<T>
    This is a special flow EBC implementation that joins together a process and a signal flow and thus implements the interfaces ProcessAndResultFlow and StartAndResultFlow.
    JoinSignals
    This is a special flow EBC implementation that joins together two signal flows.
    JoinToPair<Input1,​Input2>
    This is a Join implementation that joins the two input values to a Pair.
    LoggingUtils
    This class provides some convenience methods to be used for logging in the EBCs.
    MapPairToItem1<T>
    This EBC maps its input of type Pair to the first item of the input pair.
    MapPairToItem2<T>
    This EBC maps its input of type Pair to the second item of the input pair.
    MockAction<T>
    The MockAction is an Action implementation that can be used in (unit) tests to collect the results of a tested EBC.
    MockAction0
    The MockAction0 is an Action0 implementation that can be used in (unit) tests to count the signals of a tested EBC.
    NewFlowConnector
    This class contains some static methods used to continue a DSL sentence with a new flow of EBCs
    ObjectAndCollectionOutputCreator<Input1,​Input2Element,​OutputElement>
    This JoinOutputCreator implementation takes a first input and a Collection of input elements and creates a List of output elements that contains an output element for each element present in the second input constructed together with the given first input.
    Pair<T1,​T2>
    A Pair is a container combining two other objects of known types.
    PairOutputCreator<Input1,​Input2>
    This JoinOutputCreator implementation crates Pair instances as output values.
    ProcessAndClearThreadLocalStateStore<T>
    This class implements a decorator EBC that simply forwards the processing to the next component in the flow and clears the ThreadLocalStateStore after the flows execution.
    ProcessAndResultBase<ProcessParameter,​ResultParameter>
    A base class for an EBC that CanProcess and SendsResult.
    ProcessAndResultBoard<ProcessParameter,​ResultParameter>
    A base class for a board that CanProcess and SendsResult.
    ProcessAndResultFlow<ProcessParameter,​ResultParameter>
    An EBC that is capable of processing input with a possible outcome of a result being sent.
    ProcessAndResultFlowToFunctionAdapter<ProcessParameter,​ResultParameter>
    This adapter adapts an ProcessAndResultFlow to a Function.
    ProcessAndSignalBase<ProcessParameter>
    A base class for an EBC that CanProcess and SendsSignal.
    ProcessAndSignalBoard<ProcessParameter>
    A base class for a board that CanProcess and SendsSignal.
    ProcessAndSignalFlow<ProcessParameter>
    An EBC that is capable of processing input with a possible outcome of a signal being sent.
    ProcessBase<ProcessParameter>
    A base class for an EBC that CanProcess.
    ProcessBoard<ProcessParameter>
    A base class for a board that CanProcess.
    ReflectionUtils
    This class defines some Reflection utility methods used by the generic Join EBCs.
    ResultBase<ResultParameter>
    A base class for an EBC that SendsResult.
    ResultBoard<ResultParameter>
    A base class for a board that SendsResult.
    SendsResult<ResultParameter>
    An EBC that SendsResult is capable of sending the output of it's work to subscribed listeners and thus provides an Event to do so.
    SendsResultConnector<T>
    Instances of this class allow the DSL like definition of EBC flows by attaching the next EBC to a flow that ended with a SendsResult or Event.
    SendsSignal
    An EBC that SendsSignal is capable of sending a signal when it's work completes to subscribed listeners and thus provides an Event0 to do so.
    SendsSignalConnector
    Instances of this class allow the DSL like definition of EBC flows by attaching the next EBC to a flow that ended with a SendsSignal or Event0.
    SignalBase
    A base class for an EBC that SendsSignal.
    SignalBoard
    A base class for a board that SendsSignal.
    SplitProcess<Parameter>
    The SplitProcess distributes the process and its parameter to multiple subscribers.
    SplitProcessToSignal<Parameter>
    The SplitProcessToSignal distributes the process and its parameter to multiple regular subscribers and to multiple signal subscribers.
    SplitSignal
    The SplitSignal distributes the signal to multiple subscribers.
    StartAndClearThreadLocalStateStore
    This class implements a decorator EBC that simply forwards the processing to the next component in the flow and clears the ThreadLocalStateStore after the flows execution.
    StartAndResultBase<ResultParameter>
    A base class for an EBC that CanStart and SendsResult.
    StartAndResultBoard<ResultParameter>
    A base class for a board that CanStart and SendsResult.
    StartAndResultFlow<ResultParameter>
    An EBC that is capable of being invoked with a possible outcome of a result being sent.
    StartAndResultFlowToSupplierAdapter<ResultParameter>
    This adapter adapts an StartAndResultFlow to a Supplier.
    StartAndSignalBase
    A base class for an EBC that CanStart and SendsSignal.
    StartAndSignalBoard
    A base class for a board that CanStart and SendsSignal.
    StartAndSignalFlow
    An EBC that is capable of being invoked with a possible outcome of a signal being sent.
    StartBase
    A base class for an EBC that CanStart.
    StartBoard
    A base class for a board that CanStart.
    State<Value>
    This interface represents a state that can be hold by an EBC.
    StateFactory
    A StateFactory is used to create a new State instances.
    ThreadLocalStateFactory
    A StateFactory implementation that creates ThreadLocalState instances
    ThreadLocalStateStore
    The ThreadLocalStateStore has the responsibility to save the state values per ThreadLocalState and per Thread.
    ValueFactory<Value>
    The ValueFactory is used to create the initial value for a State hold by an EBC.
